title: Navajo National Monument: History & Culture
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     History & Culture             History & Culture        Small pots in Keet Seel Marc Steuben         White fir log across the entrance of Keet Seel. Marc Steuben  The Ancestral Puebloan people farmed the canyons, enabling them to flourish in this high desert environment. They hunted wild game and grew corn, beans, and squash.        Betatakin Marc Steuben  Like Keet Seel, Betatakin was constructed of sandstone, mud mortar, and wood.        Keet Seel Marc Steuben  Most of keet Seel has remained unchanged for 700 years.
